Albert Fritz has resigned from the DA. This follows his leader, Western Cape Premier Alan Winde firing him as Community Safety MEC, after receiving an independent investigation report. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail has more. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Former Western Cape Community Safety MEC Albert Fritz has labelled his dismissal an 'anonymous and protected political smear'. Western Cape Premier Alan Winde fired Fritz after an independent investigation found that sexual misconduct allegations against him were sufficiently credible. READ: Albert Fritz resigns from the DA Fritz has hit back, saying that he was never provided with the initial allegations against him nor was he allowed to question witnesses. He says only one witness corroborated one of the allegations which was in turn refuted by other witnesses. While the premier has refused Fritz's request to access the report, he will be taking it on review.